"Adult dependent care program" means:
An adult day care facility regulated under Title 14, Subtitle 2 of this article;
An assisted living program facility regulated under Subtitle 18 of this title;
A group home regulated under Title 10, Subtitle 5 or Title 7, Subtitle 6 of this article;
A home health agency regulated under Subtitle 4 of this title;
A congregate housing services program regulated under Title 10, Subtitle 2 of the Human Services Article;
A residential service agency as defined under § 19-4A-01 of this title;
An alternative living unit as defined under § 7-101 of this article;
A hospice facility regulated under Subtitle 9 of this title; or
A related institution regulated under Subtitle 3 of this title.

"Conviction" means a:
Plea or verdict of guilty;
Plea of nolo contendere;
Disposition of probation before judgment; or
Disposition of not criminally responsible.

"Private agency" means a person that:
Is licensed as a private detective agency under Title 13, Subtitle 3 of the Business Occupations and Professions Article;
Maintains an errors and omissions insurance policy in an amount not less than $1,000,000;
Offers customer assistance in the use of background checks for employment purposes; and
Is capable of conducting a background check within the State within 2 working days of a request and outside the State within 5 working days of a request.
